    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What conveyors are used in warehouses and distribution centers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Warehouses use belt conveyors for parcel transport, roller conveyors for case and tote handling, sortation conveyors (shoe, crossbelt, tilt-tray, pop-up wheel) for order routing, accumulation conveyors for staging, merge conveyors for combining flows, and spiral conveyors or vertical reciprocating conveyors for elevation changes. MDR (motor-driven roller) conveyors are increasingly standard for zone-controlled accumulation and energy efficiency." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a sortation conveyor?",
